# Fetch Coder CLI Integration

## Overview

The CLI was removed from this project to keep the VS Code extension focused.
A backup lives at `~/Desktop/fetch-coder-cli/`.

## How to Add CLI Back

### 1. Copy CLI folder back

```bash
cp -r ~/Desktop/fetch-coder-cli ./cli
```

### 2. Add CLI to package.json workspaces

```json
"workspaces": [
  ".",
  "cli"
]
```

### 3. Add CLI scripts to package.json

```json
"cli:link": "cd cli && npm run link",
"cli:build": "npm run protos && cd cli && npm run build",
"cli:run": "node cli/dist/cli.mjs",
"cli:build:production": "cd cli && npm run build:production",
"cli:watch": "cd cli && npm run watch",
"cli:test": "cd cli && npm run test",
"cli:dev": "cd cli && npm run dev",
"cli:unlink": "cd cli && npm run unlink"
```

### 4. Update check-types script

```json
"check-types": "npm run protos && npx tsc --noEmit && cd webview-ui && npx tsc --noEmit && cd ../cli && npx tsc --noEmit"
```

### 5. Install dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

### 6. Build and test

```bash
npm run cli:build
npm run cli:test
```

## CLI Architecture

- **Entry:** `cli/src/index.ts` — Commander.js commands
- **UI:** React Ink TUI (terminal UI)
- **Agent:** Same core agent as VS Code extension (`src/core/`)
- **API:** Same ASI:One API (`https://api.asi1.ai/v1`, model `asi1`)
- **Storage:** File-based (same pattern as extension, different host)

## Key Points

- CLI does NOT affect VS Code extension — they are independent
- CLI shares `src/core/` and `src/shared/` code with the extension
- CLI has its own `cli/package.json` with separate dependencies
- CLI needs `npm run protos` before building (same as extension)
